sentences: Omar Grant is an American Music executive who originally worked as the Road manager for Destiny's Child and now the Co-President of Roc Nation Records.
In 2006, Grant accepted a position as the creative director of urban A&R for EMI followed by senior director of A&R at Epic Records and A&R at Roc Nation.
In 2015, Grant worked as an A&R on the soundtrack for the DreamWorks animated film entitled "Home".
Omar in 2010–11 was the A&R for Kelly Rowland's album "Here I am", that featured the hit Single "Motivation" which went #1 for eight weeks on the Urban Hip Hop Charts.
